Note = {11th International Conference on Technology, Education and Development
   (INTED), Valencia, SPAIN, MAR 06-08, 2017},
Abstract = {National defense and security agendas, which often arise during times of
   crisis, tend to focus the goals of language study on narrow subjects.
   The master's degree program ``Forensic language expertise{''} offered by
   Southern Ural State University (Russian Federation) for bachelors of
   Linguistics, Philology, Law, and Psychology concerns the analysis of
   written and spoken language for legal purposes: principles and methods
   of linguistics are applied to the language of legal proceedings and
   documents. The program is designed to form the skills that allow
   students to work as experts providing a wide spectrum of expertise:
   speech analysis (meaning analysis), stylistic analysis, phonoscopic
   expertise, authorship identification, handwriting and forensic language
   expertise. The program ``Forensic language expertise{''} includes theory
   and practice of Forensic Linguistics, the following specialist-area
   disciplines: theory of language, modern Russian language,
   sociolinguistics, psycholinguistics, stylistics and literary editing,
   fundamentals of NLP (natural language processing), fundamentals of
   forensic language expertise, techniques of analyzing the written speech,
   audio and sound record phonoscopic expertise, authorship identification,
   and handwriting expertise. Practical courses are taught by leading
   experts in the field. Students learn how to use a multi-dimensional
   approach that incorporates traditional principles of language analysis
   and those of sociolinguistics, psycholinguistics, and forensic language
   expertise as well as special software and instruments for expertise (SIS
   II Sound Editor, AIPlugins, EdiTracker, Sound Cleaner modules, etc.).},
