Abstract = {Nowadays, the surveillance of criminal activities requires constant
   human monitoring. Most of these activities are happening due to handheld
   weapons mainly pistol and gun. Object detection algorithms have been
   used in detecting weapons like knives and handguns. Handgun and knives
   detection are one of the most challenging tasks due to occlusion,
   variation in viewpoint and background cluttering that occurs frequently
   in a scene. This paper reviewed and categorized various algorithms that
   have been used in the detection of handgun and knives with their
   strengths and weaknesses.},
